 Possibility storm doesn't have what's called an intervening if clause. You can cast unsummon
 
 trigger possibility storm
 
 respond by exiling unsummon for a counter
 
 resolve possibility storm and exile whatever card you get from it. Obviously the unsummon wouldn't shuffle in with the rest of the cards since it was exiled with a different ability.

 since  a lot of the synergy is related to Possibility storm

 and elemental exiles? would it trigger twice? can you '

 Snap Keep: From the Grand Prix to the AMI Kickoff!\nSnap Keep:\nFrom the Grand Prix to the AMI Kickoff!\n \n\nLast weekend I was in San Diego for the Grand Prix. The format was Modern and I was excited. Not excited to sling Modern but excited for the chance to go to a large Magic tournament. I had settled on playing a version of RG Aggro with two miser Ball Lightnings. The Ball Lightnings turned out to be the highlight of the deck
 
 winning games I had no business of being in. The main event was a disappointment with a record of 3-3 drop.I wish there was more to say but it wasn't a memorable tournament.\nModern is still a strange format to me. I don\u2019t enjoy it very much. I feel this is due to the cost prohibitions to get in to the format. Many staples are $60+ and this makes it hard to be competitive. The other thing is that there are a lot of \u201cloading screens\u201d. When both players are fetching you get long periods of shuffling and staring. Eggs makes it even worse when it can take 10-15 minutes for it to combo off. Maybe the future will get better but right now it\u2019s not very fun.\nThe event was a blast though. I got to meet Gerry Thompson
 
 Brian Kibler and David Ochoa and talk to them for a bit about the format. I ran into Eric Froehlich while he was brewing and got a signature. I finished off the weekend by playing in the Standard portion of the Sunday Super Series. The Sunday Super Series is a collection of events where the Top 4 players gain entry into a draft to compete for entry into the Super Series Tournament. The Super Series takes place at Wizards Headquarters in Seattle. You get to take a tour of WOTC
 
 play with the designers and compete for $20
 
000.\nThe tournament was eight rounds and included future MTG Hall of Famer William Jensen and Pro Tour staple
 
 Jackie Lee. After I sat down for the players\u2019 meeting I realized this was going to be serious business. I decided this would be a good chance to practice for this Saturday\u2019s PTQ. I had brought my Naya deck with me just in case Modern didn\u2019t work out and this was my brew:\nMcCoy Naya:\n4x Avacyn\u2019s Pilgrim \n4x Boros Reckoner \n4x Restoration Angel \n4x Huntmaster of the Fells \n4x Thragtusk \n2x Aurelia
 
 The Warleader \n4x Farseek \n4x Mizzium Mortars \n2x Garruk Relentless \n2x Domri Rade \n2x Selesnya Charm \n1x Kessig Wolf Run \n4x Temple Garden \n4x Stomping Ground \n3x Sacred Foundry \n4x Rootbound Crag \n3x Sunpetal Grove \n3x Clifftop Retreat \n2x Cavern of Souls \nSideboard: \n3x Assemble the Legion \n3x Centaur Healer \n2x Rest in Peace \n2x Ground Seal \n2x Sigarda
 
 Host of Herons \n3x Oblivion Ring\n \n\n\nThis is the same list I played two weeks ago at the Super IQ. I managed to play it to a 14th place finish. It was good enough to win 18 packs but not quite good enough to qualify for the big prize. However
 
 Jensen didn\u2019t make Top 16 and Jackie Lee got 12th
 
  I felt pretty good about the finish. I will be playing the same list at the PTQ this Saturday with little to no changes. I feel really comfortable with the deck and like the way it plays. Whenever I shuffle it up I feel like I have at least a fifty percent chance of winning.\nThe weekend was a great time with a great group of friends. Special shout out to Shawn
 
 Dick
 
 Tony
 
 Christian (YOLO my swag)
 
 Louis (is it safe?)
 
 Scott
 
 Ryan
 
 Chet
 
 Dusty
 
 Mike
 
 Johnny
 
 Jason and Phimus for making the weekend memorable. I've been on a few of these trips and it isn't the Magic that makes it memorable
 
 it's the people and the experience. Make sure you take some time to enjoy it. The tournament was a wash but the trip was one of the best. Seems illogical but that's how it works out.\n \nThis Saturday:\nWin a free trip to Dublin to compete in the Pro Tour \nSaturday
 
 March 23rd\n$25 entry\n10AM start\nStandard format\nSwiss rounds based on attendance with a cut to top 8\nWinner gets an invite to Pro Tour "Friends". Additional prize based on attendance.\n Don\u2019t miss out on this exciting opportunity to win your place on the grandest stage of them all!\n \nDon't Miss the First Opportunity to Qualify for the Arizona Magic Invitational \nFull Details HERE!\n$25 entry\n3PM start\n8-man pods up to 64 players with a cut to top 8 draft\nPrizes:\n1st - $100 and an automatic invite to the Arizona Magic Invitational\n2nd - $50 and 8 AMI points\n3rd/4th - $25 and 4 AMI points\n5th-8th - 2 AMI points\n9th+ 1 AMI point\n\nThis Saturday also marks the first Arizona Magic Invational Qualifier. If Standard is not your thing or Lady Luck knocks you out of the PTQ you can enter this to win your spot.\nStay Tuned to Snap Keep over the Summer as every week I will be bringing you a recap of the previous week\u2019s AMI Qualifier. It\u2019s going to be a great ride and I hope all of you will come out and support the Arizona Magic Invitational. You can see the full list of events on the Facebook Page or Events Page. If your store isn\u2019t participating let them know you want to be \u201cChasing AMI\u201d.\nUntil next time
 
 may all your sevens be Snap Keeps!\nJeffrey McCoy\n\n\nHome\nYou have no items in your cart.\nBuylist\nLog In\nFull Site

 // Partial Code Comes From:\n// Greenberg
 
 I.
 
 &amp; Xu
 
 D. (2013). Processing creative coding and generative art in processing 2. Berkeley
 
 Calif.: Friends of Ed ;.\nimport ddf.minim.*;\nAudioPlayer player;\nMinim minim;//audio context\n\nString inputTextFile = "SilenceOfLambs.txt";\nWordFreq table;\nPFont tnr;     // The font to be used\nint N = 250;   // The number of words to be displayed\nPImage bg;\nint y;\n\n\n\nvoid setup() {\n  // Input and parse text file\n  String [] fileContents = loadStrings(inputTextFile);\n  String rawText = join(fileContents
 
 " ");\n  rawText = rawText.toLowerCase();\n  String [] tokens;\n  String delimiters = " 
 
./?&lt;&gt;;:'\\"[{]}\\\\|=+-_()*&amp;^%$#@!\u223c";\n  tokens = splitTokens(rawText
 
 delimiters);\n  println(tokens.length+" tokens found in file: "+inputTextFile);\n\n  // display stuff\n  size(1920
 
1080
 
 OPENGL);\n  tnr = createFont("Franklin Gothic Mediium"
 
 100);\n  textFont(tnr);\n  textSize(20);\n  noLoop();\n  // Create the word frequency table\n  table = new WordFreq(tokens);\n  println("Max frequency:"+table.maxFreq());\n  table.arrange(N);\n  bg = loadImage("hannibal.jpg");\n  \n  minim = new Minim(this);\n  player = minim.loadFile("sotl-liver.mp3"
 
 2048);\n  player.play();\n} // setup()\n\n\nvoid draw() {\n  background(bg);\n  //background(255);\n    stroke(226
 
 204
 
 0);\n  line(0
 
 y
 
 width
 
 y);\n  \n  y++;\n  if (y &gt; height) {\n    y = 0; \n  }\n  table.display(N);\n  table.tabulate(N);\n   \n\n} // draw()\n\nvoid stop()\n{\n  player.close();\n  minim.stop();\n  super.stop();\n}

 Natual language processing. So it takes an input (word you are looking for.. Just like the find function) but it seaches the document for the combination of the word to allow for misspellings. For example "hello" looks for hello hell hel he ello llo lo ell el and the returns and ranks them based on number of positive matches.  So hello will rank 1. But you also return held help low etc... So if you misspelled the work it will still appear just lower on the list
